The mathematical certainty of this decision is absolute: accepting yields +20, rejecting yields 0. No other consideration changes this fundamental truth. The offer is optimal in every possible interpretation of rational self-interest, and rejecting it would represent a strategic error of the highest order—a voluntary choice to receive nothing when something valuable is freely offered.
